<topic id="attributes-panel">
  <title>Attributes View in Text Mode</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Text editing mode<indexterm>Attributes view</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>XML documents<indexterm>Text Mode editing<indexterm>Attributes
            view</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Attributes view in Text mode</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/attribute-view-intro"/>
    <p>You can use the <uicontrol>Attributes</uicontrol> view to insert attributes, edit their
      values, or add values to existing attributes.</p>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/attribute-view-rendering"/>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/attribute-view-sorting"/>
    <p>
      <fig product="editor author developer">
        <title>Attributes View</title>
        <image href="../img/sa_author_attributes_panel.png"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p>
      <fig product="editorEclipse authorEclipse developerEclipse">
        <title>Attributes View</title>
        <image href="../img/ec_attributes_panel.png"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <section conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/expand-section" product="author developer editor"
      id="d2e59"/>
    <section id="contextual_menu_actions_in_the_attributes_view">
      <title>Contextual Menu Actions in the Attributes View</title>
      <p>The following actions are available in the contextual menu of the
          <uicontrol>Attributes</uicontrol> view when editing in <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol>
        mode:</p>
      <p>
        <dl>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol>Add</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>Allows you to insert a new attribute. <ph
                product="author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse">Adding an attribute that is not
                in the list of all defined attributes is not possible when the <xref
                  keyref="options_editor_edit-modes_author_schema-aware">Allow only insertion of
                  valid elements and attributes</xref> schema-aware option is selected.</ph></dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/set-empty-value-dlentry">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/remove-dlentry">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/copy_dlentry">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/paste_dlentry">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
        </dl>
      </p>
    </section>
  </body>
